data.title: Cuevas through to third round after Edmund retires French Open
data.meta_description: PARIS, May 30 (Reuters) - Uruguay's Pablo Cuevas reached the third round of the French Open after Kyle Edmund, the last British man left in the  singles draw,
data.text:
ByReuters

Published 30/05/2019 at 11:40 GMT

PARIS, May 30 (Reuters) - Uruguay's Pablo Cuevas reached the third round of the French Open after Kyle Edmund, the last British man left in the singles draw, retired injured midway through the third set on Thursday.

Eurosport

Image credit: Eurosport

Edmund called on the trainer while trailing 7-6(3) 6-3 2-1 and after a short discussion, he informed the umpire he was unable to continue.

Cuevas will next play either Austrian fourth seed Dominic Thiem or Kazakhstan's Alexander Bublik.

Edmund's exit left women's 26th seed Johanna Konta as the only Briton left in the singles competition.
